# 📈 Stock Data Intelligence Dashboard

## 🚀 Overview

A full-stack stock market dashboard that fetches real-time data, processes it using data analysis techniques, and visualizes insights through an interactive web interface.

This project demonstrates backend API development, data transformation, and frontend visualization along with a simple predictive analytics feature.

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack

### 🔹 Backend

* FastAPI (Python)
* Pandas
* yfinance

### 🔹 Frontend

* HTML, CSS, JavaScript
* Chart.js

### 🔹 Deployment

* Backend: Render
* Frontend: GitHub Pages

---

## 📊 Features

### 🔹 Data Collection

* Fetches real-time stock data using yfinance API
* Supports NSE stocks (e.g., INFY.NS, TCS.NS)

### 🔹 Data Processing

* Handles missing values and formatting
* Converts date columns properly
* Calculates key financial metrics:

  * Daily Return
  * 7-day Moving Average
  * 52-week High/Low
  * Volatility (custom metric)

---

## 🔗 REST APIs

| Endpoint            | Method | Description                          |
| ------------------- | ------ | ------------------------------------ |
| `/companies`        | GET    | List available companies             |
| `/data/{symbol}`    | GET    | Last 30 days stock data              |
| `/summary/{symbol}` | GET    | 52-week high, low, average           |
| `/compare`          | GET    | Compare two stocks                   |
| `/predict/{symbol}` | GET    | Predict next price (simple ML logic) |

---

## 📈 Dashboard Features

* 📊 Interactive stock price chart
* 🔁 Compare two stocks
* 📉 Trend detection (Uptrend / Downtrend)
* ⚡ Volatility indicator
* 💬 Mock sentiment analysis
* 🤖 Price prediction (basic ML logic)

---

## 🧠 Custom Metrics

* **Volatility**: Rolling standard deviation of daily returns
* **Sentiment**: Derived from price movement (positive/negative)
* **Prediction**: Simple momentum-based next price estimation

---

## ▶️ How to Run Locally

### 🔹 Backend

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app:app --reload
```

### 🔹 Frontend

Open:

```bash
frontend/index.html
```

---

## 🌐 Deployment

* Backend hosted on Render
* Frontend hosted on GitHub Pages

